448
00:27:02,750 --> 00:27:04,542
She is squandering
her inheritance--

449
00:27:04,583 --> 00:27:07,041
Captain, this novel and
everything Data just described

450
00:27:07,083 --> 00:27:09,917
seems to be exactly what's
happening at this hotel.

451
00:27:10,959 --> 00:27:12,417
Extraordinary.

452
00:27:12,458 --> 00:27:13,625
RIKER: There's also
one other thing.

453
00:27:13,667 --> 00:27:15,291
A diary with only one entry,

454
00:27:15,333 --> 00:27:17,959
obviously made
by Colonel Richey.

455
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:19,166
PICARD: Can you read it?

456
00:27:19,208 --> 00:27:20,625
Yes.

457
00:27:20,667 --> 00:27:22,250
"I write this in the hope

458
00:27:22,291 --> 00:27:24,458
"that it will someday
be read by human eyes.

459
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,166
"I can only surmise
at this point,

460
00:27:26,208 --> 00:27:29,166
"but apparently our exploratory
shuttle was contaminated

461
00:27:29,208 --> 00:27:30,792
"by an alien life-form

462
00:27:30,834 --> 00:27:34,208
"which infected and killed
all personnel except myself.

463
00:27:34,250 --> 00:27:38,375
"I awakened to find myself
here in the Royale Hotel

464
00:27:38,417 --> 00:27:41,458
"precisely as described in
the novel I found in my room.

465
00:27:41,500 --> 00:27:46,625
"And for the last 38 years
I have survived here.

466
00:27:46,667 --> 00:27:50,208
"I have come to understand
that the alien contaminators

467
00:27:50,250 --> 00:27:53,375
"created this place for me
out of some sense of guilt,

468
00:27:53,417 --> 00:27:56,208
"presuming that the novel
we had on board the shuttle

469
00:27:56,250 --> 00:27:57,583
"about the Hotel Royale

470
00:27:57,625 --> 00:28:01,125
"was in fact a guide to
our preferred lifestyle

471
00:28:01,166 --> 00:28:03,333
"and social habits.

472
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:06,709
"Obviously, they thought this
was the world from which I came.

473
00:28:06,750 --> 00:28:09,041
"I hold no malice
toward my benefactors.

474
00:28:09,083 --> 00:28:10,709
"They could not possibly
know the hell

475
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:12,041
"that they have
put me through.

476
00:28:12,083 --> 00:28:14,875
"For it was such
a badly written book

477
00:28:14,917 --> 00:28:18,250
"filled with endless cliche
and shallow characters.

478
00:28:19,625 --> 00:28:22,583
I shall welcome death
when it comes."

479
00:28:27,834 --> 00:28:30,583
I understand,
Number One.

480
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:33,875
Now, we know why
all that is there,

481
00:28:33,917 --> 00:28:36,625
