00:34:49,709 --> 00:34:52,542
a second-rate novel.

597
00:34:52,583 --> 00:34:56,250
BELLBOY: ...Rita, she could
do something with her life.

598
00:34:56,291 --> 00:34:58,333
With your permission, sir.

599
00:34:58,375 --> 00:35:00,542
MICKEY D:
She's somebody, she's my girl.

600
00:35:00,583 --> 00:35:01,959
BELLBOY:
You got her on the stuff.

601
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,792
That's the only reason
she stays with you.

602
00:35:03,834 --> 00:35:05,542
Because you
feed her sickness.

603
00:35:05,583 --> 00:35:07,875
You gotta let me help her.

604
00:35:10,458 --> 00:35:13,417
Well, why don't we just go
outside and talk about it?

605
00:35:14,834 --> 00:35:16,583
Just watch yourself.

606
00:35:16,625 --> 00:35:18,417
Don't worry.

607
00:35:24,917 --> 00:35:26,875
It's all part
of the novel.

608
00:35:26,917 --> 00:35:28,792
Don't interfere.

609
00:35:34,917 --> 00:35:36,458
(<i> screams</i> )

610
00:35:55,417 --> 00:35:58,000
You shoulda listened
to me, kid.

611
00:35:58,041 --> 00:36:01,333
No woman's
worth dying for.

612
00:36:01,375 --> 00:36:05,709
Killing for, not dying for.

613
00:36:24,875 --> 00:36:26,375
Riker to<i> Enterprise.</i>

614
00:36:26,417 --> 00:36:28,041
Yes, Number One.

615
00:36:28,083 --> 00:36:30,750
RIKER: A bizarre incident
just took place.

616
00:36:30,792 --> 00:36:33,709
The shoot-out between
the bellboy and Mickey D.

